<div class="accordion-container">
<h2 class="section-title">
<span class="line"></span> Codes and Regulations for Opening a Child Daycare
</h2>
<details class="accordion-item">
<summary class="accordion-header">
Building Department</summary>
<div class="accordion-content">
<ul>
    <li>Day Care Centers&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
<ul style="margin-left: 40px;">
    <li>Group E, Educational (IBC Section 305.2) or Group I, Institutional (IBC Section 308.5 and IBC Section 308.5.1)&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
<ul>
    <li>Group Child Care Homes</li>
</ul>
<ul style="margin-left: 40px;">
    <li>A modification of the IRC Section 308.5.4 for&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
<ul>
    <li>Family Child Care Home</li>
</ul>
<ul style="margin-left: 40px;">
    <li>IBC Sections 305.2.3 and 308.5.4. Requires State mod for more than three children.&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
</div>
</details>
<details class="accordion-item">
<summary class="accordion-header">
Health Department</summary>
<div class="accordion-content">
<ul>
    <li>Health Department review only required for Group Child Care Homes and Child Care Centers.</li>
    <li>Comprehensive lead test required for pre-1978 buildings includes test of paint, water and bare soil.&nbsp;</li>
    <li>Food preparation or delivery for daycares must be discussed with the Department of Health and Human Services, Division of Environmental Health and Inspections.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</details>
<details class="accordion-item">
<summary class="accordion-header">
Engineering Bureau</summary>
<div class="accordion-content">
<ul>
    <li>All development projects must comply with&nbsp;<a href="https://www.stamfordct.gov/home/showpublisheddocument/4571/637540965906770000" target="_blank">Stamford’s Stormwater Drainage Manual</a>.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
    <li>Change of use applications may require the implementation of water quality improvement measures.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</details>
<details class="accordion-item">
<summary class="accordion-header">
Transportation, Traffic, &amp; Parking Department</summary>
<div class="accordion-content">
<ul>
    <li>Parking area safety considerations (geometry, signage, pavement markings)&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
<ul>
    <li>Drop-off/pick-up safety and traffic flow&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
</div>
</details>
<details class="accordion-item">
<summary class="accordion-header">
What kind of Zoning approval do I need?</summary>
<div class="accordion-content">
<ul>
    <li>Review&nbsp;<a href="https://www.stamfordct.gov/home/showpublisheddocument/2425/638568334405470000" target="_blank">Zoning Regulations</a>&nbsp;to determine if you need a Zoning Permit (staff level) for as-of-right projects or Special Permit (Zoning Board) before you begin.&nbsp; &nbsp;</li>
</ul>
</div>
</details>
<details class="accordion-item">
<summary class="accordion-header">
Zoning Review Process</summary>
<div class="accordion-content">
<ul type="disc">
    <li><strong>Family Child Care Homes</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong>Group Child Care Homes</strong>&nbsp;are allowed by Zoning Permit in all Zoning Districts except Industrial Districts.&nbsp;</li>
    <li><strong>Child Day Care Centers</strong>&nbsp;are permitted by right in commercial and multifamily zoned districts.&nbsp;</li>
    <li><strong>Child Day Care Centers</strong>&nbsp;in single-family zoning districts require a Special Permit from the Zoning Board.&nbsp;</li>
    <li>No child day care allowed in Industrial Zoning Districts.&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
</div>
</details>
<details class="accordion-item">
<summary class="accordion-header">
Parking, Drop-off/Pick-up</summary>
<div class="accordion-content">
<ul>
    <li>Parking requirement – 1.25 parking spaces per employee on maximum shift. Show assigned/shared parking spaces in survey/aerial image.&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
<ul>
    <li>Shared parking approval requires administrative approval by Zoning Board.&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
</div>
</details>
<details class="accordion-item">
<summary class="accordion-header">
Fire Marshal</summary>
<div class="accordion-content">
<ul>
    <li>Applicable Fire Codes&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
<ul>
    <li>Daycare Occupancies – NFPA 101 sec. 3.3.198.4&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
<ul>
    <li>Group Daycare – NFPA 101 sec. 17.6 (3-12 individuals)&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
<ul>
    <li>Home Daycare – NFPA 101 sec. 17.6.1.4.1.1. (3-6 individuals)&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
<ul>
    <li>Applicable Egress for daycare type&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
<ul>
    <li>Applicable Life Safety Systems&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
<ul>
    <li>Fire Alarm&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
<ul>
    <li>Smoke / CO Detection&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
<ul>
    <li>Fire Drills / Evacuation Map&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
<ul>
    <li>Exit Signage / Emergency Lights / Extinguishers&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
<ul>
    <li>For additional information, call the Fire Marshal Office at 203-977-4651</li>
</ul>
</div>
</details>
</div>
